# Tailwind-Only Styling (Intralox Sites)

**Client requirement:** All Sitecore rendering components MUST use **Tailwind utilities** for visual styling. Do not add or extend plain CSS, SCSS, or CSS modules for components.

## Prohibited (component work)

- **New or modified** `src/assets/components/<component>.scss` (per-component global SCSS)
- **CSS modules** (`*.module.css`) imported from `src/components/**`
- **Plain CSS files** colocated with components for layout/color/typography
- **`styled-components`**, **`@emotion`**, or other CSS-in-JS for component chrome
- **Global selectors** targeting a component (e.g. `.component.footer a { }`) — use Tailwind on the element instead
- **Generic Tailwind palette** when an `@theme` token exists (`bg-white`, `text-gray-900`, `border-gray-200`)

## Required pattern (Intralox)

1. **Tailwind classes inside JSX** — literal strings on `className`.
2. **`cn()` for conditional assignments** only (`params`, CMS, state, `params.styles`) on that same node (see `cn-conditional-only.mdc`).
3. **No constants** for Tailwind strings — no top-level `const FOO_CLASS`, no `*Classes.ts`, no class maps in `*Utils.ts`.
4. **No separate style files** unless Tailwind cannot be applied to the JSX node (document the reason in PR).
5. During migration, inline legacy `componentShellClasses` / `*Classes.ts` imports when touching that component.
4. **Design-system tokens** from `src/assets/base/variables.scss` (`@theme`) — e.g. `bg-surface`, `text-ink-primary`, `border-stroke-default`.
5. **SXA wrappers** unchanged: `component`, `component-content`, plus `params.styles` on the root.

```tsx
// ✅ Inline on every element
<section className="box-border w-full min-w-0">
<article className="flex flex-col rounded-xl border border-stroke-default">

// ✅ Conditional — cn() on the node only
<div className={cn('flex gap-4', isActive && 'bg-surface-subtle', styles)}>

// ❌ WRONG — top-level class const (even private, even repeated)
const CARD_SHELL_CLASS = 'flex flex-col rounded-xl';
<article className={CARD_SHELL_CLASS}>

// ❌ WRONG — class builder in utils
export function getFooterNavClass() { return '…'; }

// ❌ WRONG — new component SCSS file
// src/assets/components/my-component.scss
```

## Allowed (narrow exceptions)

| Allowed | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `variables.scss` (`@theme`) | Token source of truth — add tokens here, not component SCSS |
| `main.scss` / `globals.css` | Tailwind entry, variants, framework imports only |
| `src/assets/components/container.scss` etc. | Legacy global SXA resets — **do not extend** for new components |
| Inline `style={{ }}` | **Only** dynamic CSS variables (`--timeline-event-img-ar`, aspect ratios) — not colors/spacing/layout |
| Tailwind arbitrary values | Only when no `@theme` token exists; prefer adding a token |
| `!` modifiers (`p-0!`) | Override SXA `.component` padding where documented |

## When editing an existing component that still has SCSS

- **Migrate styling to Tailwind** in the same change (colocate in the **`.tsx`** / `partial/` that renders the UI).
- **Delete** the component SCSS file and remove its `@import` from `src/assets/components/index.scss`.
- Do not leave two sources of truth (SCSS + Tailwind).

## Body / scroll / portaled UI

- Scroll lock, focus traps: **JavaScript** (`useEffect` on `document.body`), not global `body.foo` CSS classes.
- Portaled dropdowns/modals: Tailwind `fixed`, `z-[…]`, `pointer-events` on the portal root.

## PR checklist (styling) — IT-0

- [ ] No new `*.scss` under `assets/components/` for the feature
- [ ] No new `*.module.css` under `src/components/`
- [ ] No new `*Classes.ts` and no layout `*_CLASS` / maps in `*Utils.ts`
- [ ] **All** layout classes **inline** on JSX (zero top-level class consts)
- [ ] Conditionals on the rendered node use **`cn()`** in that TSX file (never `cn()` for static-only constants — see `cn-conditional-only.mdc`)
- [ ] No remaining imports from `*Classes.ts` or class builders in touched utils
- [ ] `<RichText className="…">` — typography inline on JSX (not utils constants)
- [ ] Colors use `@theme` Tailwind utilities, not raw hex in TSX/SCSS
- [ ] Visual QA at 320, 768, 992, 1200px when layout changes

